Task 35 - Introduction to Observer
Build a basic event notification system

EventManager (Subject)

Attribute: _observers (empty list)
Methods:
subscribe(observer) → adds observer to list
unsubscribe(observer) → removes observer from list
notify(event) → calls update(event) on all observers
Observer (base class)

Abstract method: update(event)
Logger and EmailAlert implement Observer

Logger.update(event) → prints [LOG] Event received: {event}
EmailAlert.update(event) → prints [EMAIL] Sending alert for: {event}
manager = EventManager()

logger = Logger()
email = EmailAlert()

manager.subscribe(logger)
manager.subscribe(email)
manager.notify("server_down")
# [LOG] Event received: server_down
# [EMAIL] Sending alert for: server_down

manager.unsubscribe(email)
manager.notify("disk_full")
# [LOG] Event received: disk_full  ← email no longer notified

One event, multiple reactions. That's Observer.

Task 36 - Observer in a Real System
Build a Stock Price tracker

Stock (Subject)

Attributes: symbol, price, _observers (list)
Methods:
subscribe(observer), unsubscribe(observer), notify()
set_price(new_price) → updates price and calls notify()
StockObserver (base)

Abstract method: update(symbol, price)
Three observers:

PriceDisplay → prints [DISPLAY] {symbol}: ${price}
PriceAlert(threshold) → prints [ALERT] {symbol} crossed ${threshold}! only if price exceeds threshold
PriceLogger → keeps a list of all prices, show_history() prints them all
stock = Stock("AAPL", 150)

display = PriceDisplay()
alert = PriceAlert(180)
logger = PriceLogger()

stock.subscribe(display)
stock.subscribe(alert)
stock.subscribe(logger)

stock.set_price(160)
# [DISPLAY] AAPL: $160
# [LOGGER] Recorded AAPL: $160

stock.set_price(185)
# [DISPLAY] AAPL: $185
# [ALERT] AAPL crossed $180!
# [LOGGER] Recorded AAPL: $185

stock.unsubscribe(display)
stock.set_price(170)
# [LOGGER] Recorded AAPL: $170  ← display no longer watching

logger.show_history()
# AAPL price history: [160, 185, 170]

Each observer decides what to do with the update — the Stock doesn't care who's watching.
